(22, 'Best Safari in Tanzania', 'best-safari-in-tanzania', '', '<h1><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Serengeti Safari: Best Safari in Tanzania</span></h1><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">With 21 national parks to choose from, you might be wondering which national park to choose for your Tanzania safari. While many travellers visit more than just one park, Serengeti is the top choice for tourists who only have time to make it to one place. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Serengeti is one of the largest national parks in Africa. With endless activities and accommodation choices, it’s by far the best safari in Tanzania. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">This guide will go over all the best reasons to visit Serengeti. And if you have more time, why not visit all the parks in the northern circuit? </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Combining Serengeti with other northern parks like Tarangire, Lake Manyara, and Ngorongoro Crater is one of the most popular safari itineraries. </span></p><p><br /></p><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tanzania’s Safari Superstar </span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mention the word safari and the first place people think of is the Serengeti. Home to the Big 5 and the Great Migration, Serengeti is not just famous for being the backdrop of the movie The Lion King. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Imagine waking up from your campsite or lodge and seeing Mt. Kilimanjaro in the distance. Hundreds of wildebeests are making their journey across the savanna to Kenya. Hippos are bathing in the local watering hole to cool off from the hot African sun. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Serengeti offers all these views and more! Many people who have been to national parks all over the world don’t hesitate to say that Serengeti is their favorite. </span></p><p><br /></p><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">See the Great Migration </span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the top experiences in Serengeti is the Great Migration. Ready to see one of the natural wonders of the world? Over 2 million wildebeests make this journey every year starting in the Ngorongoro Crater, going through Serengeti, and ending in Masai Mara in Kenya. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">About half a million gazelles and over 200,000 zebras also take part in the Great Migration. The migration starts during the calving season when thousands of calves are born every day. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nothing is more special than seeing a baby wildebeest taking its first steps with its mother. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The wildebeests are the main part of the migration because they are seeking safe homes for their new babies. As they head northwest to Masai Mara, they make a dangerous journey including crossing the Grumeti River. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">You can also see zebras crossing the Mara River as they begin their journey to Masai Mara. The river has one of the top concentrations of flora and fauna. It’s also home to all of Tanzania’s famous predators. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">You might even get to see one stalking its prey. Will they be successful? You’ll have to go to Serengeti to see for yourself! </span></p><p><br /></p><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Where the Big 5 Call Home </span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Big 5 are the greatest beasts that Serengeti has to offer. Most safari travellers bring their binoculars and the best camera lenses to ensure the best views of these magnificent animals. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Not sure what the Big 5 animals are? Here is a little more about each animal:</span></p><p><br /></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">African Leopards: These animals can be black, cream, or cream with black spots. They are often hard to see because they only come out at night. Serengeti has more big cats than other parks though, so seeing them here is your best bet! </span></li><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Lions: The ruler of the savanna is found all over the Serengeti. You’ll see them sunbathing, hiding in the bush, and catching their prey. </span></li><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Cape Buffalos: The only one of the Big 5 that is not considered an endangered species. There are plenty in the Serengeti. </span></li><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">African Elephants: Although there are more elephants in Tarangire, Serengeti still boasts an impressive population</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Black Rhinos: This animal weighs between 1,760 to 3,090 pounds. It’s one of the most endangered species in the world and Serengeti is one of the only places you can see them. </span></li></ul><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Huge Density of Wildlife</span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">With over 430 different species of animals, Serengeti is one of the top places in the world for wildlife viewing. Make sure you bring your best camera with plenty of extra memory cards as the park is full of picture-perfect backdrops. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Your safari guide can take you to different parts of the park depending on which animal you want to see. The guide usually asks you and your safari members which animals they’re most keen to view and then tries to find them in the park!</span></p><p><br /></p><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Many Ways to Explore the Ecosystems </span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Serengeti has more ecosystems than any of the other parks in Tanzania. Northern Serengeti is full of wooded areas and mountains. It’s the best part to see elephants and giraffes. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Serengeti plains are famous for their grasslands that are full of animals. Since there are no trees, you can see for miles and miles. The plains are some of the best places to see wildlife with an open view. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The western part of Serengeti has the Grumeti River and all the special species that like to live in the black clay soil near the water. You’ll see hippos, crocodiles, and monkeys. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Because of its diverse plant and animal life, Serengeti is a UNESCO World Heritage Site. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">What makes Serengeti so special is that you can explore it in many different ways. Take a game driving safari if you want to sit in the back of a jeep and drive to all the best parts of the park. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">You can also take a walking safari with an experienced guide who will take you through the bush and the plains. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">If you aren’t afraid of heights, you can even take a hot air balloon ride high in the skies of Serengeti. </span></p><p><br /></p><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Easy Starting Point for Zanzibar </span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Other than Serengeti. Zanzibar is one of the top places that brings so many travellers to Tanzania every year. Don’t worry, you don’t have to choose between Serengeti and Zanzibar. You can easily go to both! </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Safaris are specially designed to bring you from the island or take you to the island once your safari is over. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Serengeti even has two landing strips so the safari company can fly you directly to Zanzibar after your safari ends. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Many people choose to do Serengeti first and then head to Zanzibar after so they can enjoy the turquoise water and sand. However you choose to plan your trip, our company is here to help you fine-tune the details and the itinerary. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Since Zanzibar doesn\'t have any national parks of its own, spending time in mainland Tanzania to see Serengeti or other national parks is important. Luckily, transportation to and from the island is convenient and affordable. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">If you’re ready to see Tanzania’s best park and endless wildlife, a Serengeti safari is the best choice in East Africa. Combine it with other northern circuit parks to get a bigger picture of Tanzania\'s best landscapes. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">What makes Serengeti so great is that it can easily be combined with other parks and then you end your journey in Zanzibar where there are some of the most beautiful beaches in the world. </span></p><p><br /></p>', '', '', '219', 'publish', 1, '2022-12-08 09:37:24', '2022-12-13 09:42:55', NULL),
(23, 'Is a Safari in Tanzania Worth It?', 'is-safari-in-tanzania-worth-it', '', '<h1><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Is a Safari in Tanzania Worth It?</span></h1><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Without any doubt, the answer to this question is yes! Not only is a safari in Tanzania worth it, but it’s by far one of the best countries in Africa for wildlife viewing. With 22 national parks to explore, you’ll never get bored of safaris here even if you do one every year! </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">What makes Tanzania so special for safaris though? There are many reasons why safaris in Tanzania are absolutely worth it. </span></p><p><br /></p><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Best Destination for Tourists </span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Coming on a safari to Tanzania requires much budgeting and planning. Although there are many affordable options for safaris, you still want to make sure your hard-earned money is being spent well! </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tanzania can give you the most bang for your buck since there are 22 national parks, 44 game-restricted areas, 28 game reserves, two marine parks, and a conservation area. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">With parks in the north, south, and west, you can view wildlife and go for game drives in virtually every area of the country. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tanzania is also home to Mount Kilimanjaro, one of the top destinations for tourists and climbers. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">You’ll also find the famous Serengeti here. While Serengeti is the most frequented park, there are many other options for safaris. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Zanzibar is also one of the top places to visit in Tanzania with pristine beaches and laid-back island vibes. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">All of these places make Tanzania one of the top spots in Africa for tourists!</span></p><p><br /></p><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Why is Tanzania The Best Place for Safaris? </span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">When people travel to Africa for safaris, they want to make sure they have as many opportunities to see wildlife as possible. Spending the money and effort to come to Africa for a safari only to not see the animals you were hoping for can be devastating. </span></p><p><br /></p><h3><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(67, 67, 67);\">22 National Parks </span></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Since Tanzania has dozens of national parks and other places to view wildlife, there is no chance of leaving without seeing your wildlife favorites. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Serengeti is the largest of all the parks and gives you a chance to see zebras, lions, cheetahs, leopards, and hyenas. It’s also where the Great Migration takes place. Over 1.5 million animals including wildebeests can be seen crossing over to Maasai Mara in Kenya. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">After Serengeti, Ngorongoro Crater is where most tourists flock to. You can find the Big 5 here as well as many different bird species. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">After spending a day in the Ngorongoro Crater, head to Lake Manyara. This is where you’re most likely to spot tree-climbing lions. It’s also home to thousands of pink flamingos. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">If you want to see elephants more than any other animal, make sure to head to Tarangire National Park. It’s an easy park to get to from Arusha and has more elephants than any other park. </span></p><p><br /></p><h3><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(67, 67, 67);\">Parks in Every Part of the Country </span></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">While places like Serengeti and Tarangire are part of the northern circuit safaris, the north is not the only part of the country to visit for wildlife attractions. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Southern circuit safaris include Mikumi Park, Nyerere Park, and the Selous Reserve. The parks in the south offer a totally different experience including fishing for spirited tiger fish. The parks are also home to different species of monkeys and wild dogs. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">You can go fly camping to get close to crocodiles or spend the day canoeing on the Rufiji River. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ruaha National Park and Kiulo National Park are also destinations along the southern circuit parks and are especially good for travellers interested in the flora and fauna of Tanzania. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Southern circuit parks offer different experiences compared to the north. Rarer species of monkeys and birds are also found in the south. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">If you’re interested in the more remote parts of the country head to the west. There are also many game reserves in this part of the country where you can go chimpanzee trekking. </span></p><p><br /></p><h3><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(67, 67, 67);\">Mild Weather </span></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Many countries in Africa are affected by droughts, earthquakes, and flooding. Tanzania rarely sees climate issues like these. The weather is mild all year round making it a perfect safari destination no matter what time of year you plan to take your holiday. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The dry season is the most common time to visit the parks. The wet season also boasts beautiful parks though since the greenery and vegetation are more luscious. </span></p><p><br /></p><h3><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(67, 67, 67);\">Easy Travel Logistics </span></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tourism is one of Tanzania’s main sources of income. The government of Tanzania has made many moves to ensure tourists and safari travelers have easy access to all parts of the country. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">There are many airstrips in the national parks making it extremely easy to get into the parks for those who prefer not to drive. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Safari companies also pick you up from the international airports in Tanzania and take you to the parks. There is no need to rent a car or figure out the public bus system. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">All you need to do is sit back and relax as you’re chauffeured to all the places on your itinerary. </span></p><p><br /></p><h3><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(67, 67, 67);\">Endless Accommodation Options </span></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the other main reasons why Tanzania safaris are definitely worth it is because there are accommodation choices for all types of travellers. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Want to be right next to the animals and wake up to tracks through the camp? Book an adventure camping or mobile camping safari. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Prefer to be in a hotel with all modern amenities and fresh food? Book a luxury lodge complete with pools, lounges, and bars. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">There are also in-between options such as permanent tented camps for those that still want to be outdoors but have amenities like indoor bathrooms and dining halls. </span></p><p><br /></p><h3><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(67, 67, 67);\">Safaris for Every Age </span></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tanzanian safaris can be catered to all age groups. People love to bring young kids on safaris so they can learn more about wildlife and see the animals up close. It’s a magical experience for young kids to see the large mammals they have previously only seen in books. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Many safaris have game drive choices so if there is an elderly member in your party, they don’t need to worry about walking or moving around the parks. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">For the young and old, safaris in Tanzania are worth it because they are specially catered to your unique needs and desires. </span></p><p><br /></p><h3><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(67, 67, 67);\">Other Cultural Opportunities </span></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tanzania isn’t just famous for safaris. You also have plenty of other opportunities to experience African culture like never before. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Head to a Masaai village to experience traditional dancing and ceremonies. You can also partake in eating their food and learning more about their way of life. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Don’t leave Tanzania without first visiting Zanzibar where you can immerse yourself in island life. You can also tour Stone Town and see how Tanzanian culture has been influenced by other countries including Great Britain, Germany, and India. </span></p><p><br /></p><h2><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Is a Tanzania Safari Worth It?</span></h2><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yes! Safaris in Tanzania give you a unique opportunity to immerse yourself in East Africa’s best habitats and ecosystems. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tanzania offers more national parks and game reserves than any other country. You can relax on a game drive safari or be more adventurous through fly camping and chimpanzee trekking. </span></p><p><br /></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Safaris are perfect for all ages with endless options for accommodation. Since the government has heavily invested in the tourism sector, traveling through and to the parks is also extremely easy. </span></p>', '', '', '220', 'publish', 1, '2022-12-08 10:58:33', '2022-12-13 09:44:47', NULL),
